CMake Configure

Usage: cm configure [OPTIONS] [ARGS]...

Arguments:
  [ARGS]...  Trailing arguments to forward to cmake

Options:
  -p, --prefix-path <PREFIX_PATH>  Append to CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH [default: empty]
  -g, --generator <GENERATOR>      Generator [default: Ninja]
  -c, --config <CONFIG>            Build Config [default: Release]
  -m, --makefiles                  Shorthand for `-g "Unix Makefiles"`
  -d, --debug                      Shorthand for `--config Debug`
  -f, --flag <FLAG>                Append to C_FLAGS and CXX_FLAGS
  -#, --dry-run                    Perform a dry run, only printing the generated command line
      --san                        Enable ASan and UBSan
  -q, --quirks <QUIRKS>            Disable quirk mode detection and specify one explicitly [possible
                                   values: none, llvm]
  -h, --help                       Print help

LLVM-SPECIFIC OPTIONS:
      --expensive-checks
          Enable expensive checks
  -e, --enable-projects <ENABLE_PROJECTS>
          Append to LLVM_ENABLE_PROJECTS [default: llvm;clang;lld]
  -t, --targets-to-build <TARGETS_TO_BUILD>
          Append to LLVM_TARGETS_TO_BUILD [default: all]

CMAKE DIRECTORY OPTIONS:
  -s, --source <SOURCE>  CMake Source Directory
  -b, --binary <BINARY>  CMake Binary Directory
